<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="87" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="20.[227,372,729,755]" box="[227,372,729,755]" pageId="20" pageNumber="87">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,372,729,755]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="20" pageNumber="87" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,372,729,755]" pageId="20" pageNumber="87">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[226,1437,776,1014]" pageId="20" pageNumber="87">
<typeStatus box="[227,336,776,802]" pageId="20" pageNumber="87">Holotype</typeStatus>
MB.C.30461.1 is a phragmocone segment of about a quarter whorl with almost 
<quantity box="[1291,1360,776,803]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="87" unit="mm" value="9.0">9 mm</quantity>
whorl height (
<figureCitation box="[315,420,811,838]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="19.[229,272,2001,2027]" captionTargetBox="[229,1429,1620,1953]" captionTargetId="figure-320@19.[227,1437,1616,1960]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Fig. 14. Vestinautilus angulatus sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (all Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Paratype" pageId="20" pageNumber="87">Fig. 14B</figureCitation>
). It shows a triangular whorl profile with a shallow, almost flat venter that is bordered on both sides by two elevated, sharp longitudinal ridges. Flanks, umbilical wall and dorsum form a broadly curved, semi-circular unit. On the flanks there are two longitudinal ridges, which are considerably weaker than the ridges on the ventrolateral shoulder (
<figureCitation box="[858,966,917,944]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="20.[227,270,1851,1877]" captionTargetBox="[229,1433,1446,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-302@20.[229,1433,1446,1793]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Fig. 15. Vestinautilus angulatus sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (both Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Whorl profile of paratype MB.C.30462.1. B. Suture line of paratype MB.C.30462.1, at ww =14.1 mm, wh=9.0 mm.C. Whorl profile of holotype MB.C.30461.1. D. Suture line of holotype MB.C.30461.1, at ww =12.7 mm, wh= 8.8 mm. Scale bar units= 1 mm." pageId="20" pageNumber="87">Fig. 15C</figureCitation>
). The suture line shows a deep, broadly rounded outer lobe and a ventrolateral saddle which has two crests because of the two longitudinal ridges. The lateral lobe is very broad and continues into a very low internal saddle (
<figureCitation box="[1206,1315,987,1014]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="20.[227,270,1851,1877]" captionTargetBox="[229,1433,1446,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-302@20.[229,1433,1446,1793]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Fig. 15. Vestinautilus angulatus sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (both Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Whorl profile of paratype MB.C.30462.1. B. Suture line of paratype MB.C.30462.1, at ww =14.1 mm, wh=9.0 mm.C. Whorl profile of holotype MB.C.30461.1. D. Suture line of holotype MB.C.30461.1, at ww =12.7 mm, wh= 8.8 mm. Scale bar units= 1 mm." pageId="20" pageNumber="87">Fig. 15D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[227,1437,1053,1150]" pageId="20" pageNumber="87">
The 
<specimenCount box="[281,446,1053,1079]" pageId="20" pageNumber="87" type="generic" typeStatus="paratypes">two paratypes</specimenCount>
MB.C.30462.1 (
<quantity box="[648,718,1053,1079]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="87" unit="mm" value="9.0">9 mm</quantity>
wh; 
<figureCitation box="[779,886,1053,1079]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="19.[229,272,2001,2027]" captionTargetBox="[229,1429,1620,1953]" captionTargetId="figure-320@19.[227,1437,1616,1960]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Fig. 14. Vestinautilus angulatus sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (all Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Paratype" pageId="20" pageNumber="87">Fig. 14A</figureCitation>
) and MB.C.30461.2 (
<quantity box="[1147,1217,1053,1079]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="87" unit="mm" value="7.0">7 mm</quantity>
wh; 
<figureCitation box="[1278,1383,1053,1079]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="19.[229,272,2001,2027]" captionTargetBox="[229,1429,1620,1953]" captionTargetId="figure-320@19.[227,1437,1616,1960]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Fig. 14. Vestinautilus angulatus sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (all Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Paratype" pageId="20" pageNumber="87">Fig. 14C</figureCitation>
) are very similar to the 
<typeStatus box="[449,552,1088,1114]" pageId="20" pageNumber="87">holotype</typeStatus>
in conch form and suture line. The two-humped ventrolateral saddle is also pronounced in 
<typeStatus box="[403,504,1124,1150]" pageId="20" pageNumber="87">paratype</typeStatus>
MB.C.30462.1 (
<figureCitation box="[702,809,1123,1150]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="20.[227,270,1851,1877]" captionTargetBox="[229,1433,1446,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-302@20.[229,1433,1446,1793]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Fig. 15. Vestinautilus angulatus sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (both Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Whorl profile of paratype MB.C.30462.1. B. Suture line of paratype MB.C.30462.1, at ww =14.1 mm, wh=9.0 mm.C. Whorl profile of holotype MB.C.30461.1. D. Suture line of holotype MB.C.30461.1, at ww =12.7 mm, wh= 8.8 mm. Scale bar units= 1 mm." pageId="20" pageNumber="87">Fig. 15B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
