<paragraph blockId="20.[227,1437,1235,1332]" pageId="20" pageNumber="87">
<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[227,502,1235,1261]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Vestinautilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="20" pageNumber="87" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="angulatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[227,502,1235,1261]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="87">Vestinautilus angulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[511,604,1236,1262]" pageId="20" pageNumber="87" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
belongs to the few species of the genus with a moderately depressed whorl profile (ww/wh ~1.50) and a very weak longitudinal sculpture; in these respects, the new species differs from all other species of the genus in which the whorls are not embracing.
</paragraph>
